<h3 id="labels">Labels</h3>

<p>In Arizona Bootstrap, labels have been replaced with the <a href="/arizona-bootstrap/docs/0.0/components/badge">Badge</a> component. Labels can be replicated by extending the <code class="highlighter-rouge">.badge</code> styles.</p>

<div class="bd-example">
  <span class="label label-default">Default</span>
  <span class="label label-primary">Primary</span>
  <span class="label label-success">Success</span>
  <span class="label label-info">Info</span>
  <span class="label label-warning">Warning</span>
  <span class="label label-danger">Danger</span>
  <span class="label label-muted">Muted</span>
</div>

<h3 id="panels">Panels</h3>

<p>Panels have been extended using a combination of the <code class="highlighter-rouge">.card</code> class (and its child classes) and the <code class="highlighter-rouge">.bg-light</code> class. “Expanding” or “collapsible” panels, however, are still available as an Arizona Bootstrap component: <a href="/arizona-bootstrap/docs/0.0/components/collapse">Collapse</a>.</p>

